ers are tapping into a power much greater than even they realize. Something that has it's own agenda and a cruel predatory nature. Sure, and recently me and the boys are pretty well convinced that its stirring and hunting around, looking for ways to cause evil. But here's the rub Mr. T'ex. Having driven the undead from our fair valley long ago we have precious little reanimated flesh to work with. I was hoping you could pass on to your guild the request from the clerics  of Rivervale for three types of undead flesh.<br>For every complete group of three we will pay one hundred plat. Sure, and that would be a blessing for us in the fight against the beastly undead.<br>The three types needed are:<br><br>algae covered flesh from zombie sailors in the sea in Eruds crossing<br>waterlogged flesh from drowned citizens in the foul sewers in Freeport<br>swollen flesh from the horrible Greenblood zombies in the Fearrott<br><br>If any of your fine Guild members wish to help in the fight against the undead and perhaps make a tidy profit too then please have them gather these things and send me a note. I'll meet 'em in Freeport and hand over the reward and my thanks. Now I ain't saying this isn't dangerous so tell any who are interested that it is quite a tricky task. <br><br>Now I can tell from how Lady Myawl speaks of you that your a good, loving, and pious man. I don't know what deity you worship but I can tell you fight on the side of goodness and righteousness. If you And your guild could help us in this matter me and the boys at the temple would be most happy.<br>Thank you in advance.<br><br>May Bristlebane always give you a merry laugh<br><br>Yours in faith,<br><br>Neako Soulrizer <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uqveen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qveen</A> at: 11/11/01 11:56:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bdraconisrampant.sho